node.text:
Fresh batch of Invisible Touch! This unfiltered Helles-style lager, brewed using a double decoction mash, is a smooth, touch of sweet beaut. This batch uses Weyermann’s Barke Pilsner malt, our first time using this malt! We’re getting notes of honey and crisp biscuits, with a light mouthfeel and a soft but dry finish. 4.9% ABV — $17/4-pk.

Invisible Touch releases today! It will be available for shipping tomorrow. We’re open from 2-10pm with indoor bar service starting at 5pm!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Grimm Artisanal Ales on August 04, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
The return of the matchbox! Matchbox Lambo takes one of our most beloved beers, Lambo Door, and reconfigures the DIPA as a bite-sized, super crushable session IPA. Matchbox Lambo is all mango and peach on the nose — like opening a bag of Haribo gummy rings. Notes of Valencia orange pop in the flavor. The body is light and dry with a mild and refreshing bite of bitterness. 4.5% ABV — $17/4-pack

Matchbox Lambo releases today! We’re open from 2-10pm with indoor seating starting at 5!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Grimm Artisanal Ales on August 02, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Return of Afterimage! Afterimage is one of our favorite DIPAs and holds a dear place in the heart of Grimm. It's the first beer we ever canned back in 2015, the first beer we canned on our OWN canning line in 2020, and we're always excited to have it back around. Juicy, juicy, juicy with the slightest twist of dankness. Hazy orange, soft carbonation, and plush fruity aromas. Mosaic, El Dorado, and Simcoe hops deliver immense and intricate notes of mango, marmalade, pine, honeysuckle, and lemon rind. 8% ABV — $20/4-pack.

Afterimage releases today from our taproom! We’re open from 2-10, with indoor seating beginning at 5.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Grimm Artisanal Ales on July 29, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
EVERYTHING'S OK IPA. 

Brewed with Mosaic, Strata & El Dorado hops, this copacetic india pale ale delivers bright aromas of passionfruit, ripe berry, and gummy peach rings with calming, herbaceous undertones of damiana, chamomile & lemon balm. The fruit-forward nose is complemented with flavors of bittersweet candied citrus peel, lemon Italian ice and white peach. Medium-bodied with a lingering and tangy bitterness. Everything's OK! 6.6% ABV—$18/4-pk

Everything’s OK IPA 🤠 releases today! It will be available for shipping when we update our store tomorrow at noon. We’re open from 2-10pm today with indoor seating starting at 5pm.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Grimm Artisanal Ales on July 28, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
The return of Piña Pop! This pop sour brewed with pineapples, coconuts, vanilla, and milk sugar is a gentle tropical island breeze on a sunny, seaside day — for us, a refreshing reprieve from the smoggy, urban island we are located on! Notes of sweet and tangy pineapple are complemented by a vanilla-coconut cream swirl making for a perfectly crushable piña colada treat. ⁣🍍🥥🍍🥥🍍🥥🍍🥥
⁣5% ABV—$20/4-pk⁣.

Piña Pop! releases today from our taproom. We’re open from 2-10, with indoor seating beginning at 5pm.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Grimm Artisanal Ales on July 27, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
🔫 🚗 GET IN, WE’RE GOING CLEAR

ZERO COAST, our deliciously bitter and hoppy west coast DIPA is guaranteed to remove any and all hostile body thetans! The outrageously high lupulin dose broke our e-meter; we don’t even know how many IBU’s this thing has. When your palate achieves operating thetan level two you will notice that this “Sonoma-style double IPA” is inspired by Pliny The Elder. 7lbs/bbl of Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, and Amarillo deliver old-school bitter hoppy notes of citrus, pine, and Froot Loops™️. Hoppy intensity explodes from the glass, and the result is ultra clean and drinkable. How do we make this unfiltered beer so clear with the same house yeast strain we use in our hazy IPA? Maybe you’ll find out when you level up…

$20/4-pk, 8% ABV.

Zero Coast releases today from our taproom! We’re open from 2-10, with indoor seating beginning at 5.

node.text:
New batch of Destination Neon! This DIPA—brewed with Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo & Motueka—is a hazed up citrus bomb. Bright notes of tangerine, lime and ripe peach pop atop sweet treat flavors of cotton candy and orange sherbert. Medium-bodied with a juicy finish! 8% ABV.

Destination Neon releases today from our taproom! We are open from 2-10, with indoor seating beginning at 5pm.

node.text: More local fruit! We received blueberries from Pastore Orchards in neighboring New Jersey. These whole berries are currently undergoing a carbonic maceration and fermentation in their own juices. Soon we’ll rack some casks of spontaneous ale onto the fruit, sparking a secondary fermentation. Keep your eyes peeled for a release later this summer!
